title: Biscuit Tin, ""Reading & London"", 1906
markings: On underside: HUNTLEY & PALMERS BISCUITS" / "READING & LONDON"
description: Biscuit tin in the form of eight bound books, with hinged lid as marbled pages and edges of book covers; pull tab as bookmark.  The sides finished to appear as polychromed tooled leather, the front as book spines with the following titles: "History of England," Pilgrims Progress," "Burns," Pickwick Papers," "Robinson Crusoe," " Gullivers Travels," "Self Help," and "Shakespear;" all bound with simulated leather strap and buckle.
